#: ../../developer/general/gsoc.rst:231 394190ef4ec6405bba5e9664874ca566
msgid "Qubes Live USB"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/gsoc.rst:234 caa84a58297a4c27a90598889098d451
msgid "**Project**: Revive Qubes Live USB, integrate it with installer"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/gsoc.rst:236 5f805697767b4f7690aa5f6656fe5e41
msgid ""
"**Brief explanation**: Qubes Live USB is based on Fedora tools to build live"
" distributions. But for Qubes we need some adjustments: starting Xen instead"
" of Linux kernel, smarter copy-on-write handling (we run there multiple VMs,"
" so a lot more data to save) and few more. Additionally in Qubes 3.2 we have"
" so many default VMs that default installation does not fit in 16GB image "
"(default value) - some subset of those VMs should be chosen. Ideally we’d "
"like to have just one image being both live system and installation image. "
"More details: `#1552 <https://github.com/QubesOS/qubes-"
"issues/issues/1552>`__, `#1965 <https://github.com/QubesOS/qubes-"
"issues/issues/1965>`__."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/gsoc.rst:240 e029d88a8ded41a4b4185ba9c83ac601
msgid "Adjust set of VMs and templates included in live edition."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/gsoc.rst:242 71c970398cda4434859ebbc84394e959
msgid "Update and fix build scripts for recent Qubes OS version."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/gsoc.rst:244 7ecef836f50d4f5a9ec7d5ce4fb254d3
msgid ""
"Update startup script to mount appropriate directories as either copy-on-"
"write (device-mapper snapshot), or tmpfs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/gsoc.rst:246 3041dc4277c547ea8c6a4efe315527f9
msgid ""
"Optimize memory usage: should be possible to run sys-net, sys-firewall, and "
"at least two more VMs on 4GB machine. This include minimizing writes to "
"copy-on-write layer and tmpfs (disable logging etc)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/gsoc.rst:248 d32ec2c15cad48f8a34ec8742cdb7338
msgid ""
"Research option to install the system from live image. If feasible add this "
"option."
msgstr ""

