#: ../../developer/general/gsoc.rst:269 ea0035c4af534e59a05f4b6ca7520994
msgid "LogVM(s)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/gsoc.rst:272 70c1c6e0f1074a058112b92ffde2c74b
msgid "**Project**: LogVM(s)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/gsoc.rst:274 ba9f1682818c45dea475ea50a1bcc69d
msgid ""
"**Brief explanation**: Qubes AppVMs do not have persistent /var (on "
"purpose). It would be useful to send logs generated by various VMs to a "
"dedicated log-collecting VM. This way logs will not only survive VM "
"shutdown, but also be immune to altering past entries. See `#830 "
"<https://github.com/QubesOS/qubes-issues/issues/830>`__ for details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/gsoc.rst:278 3cef3ca1c71446159261d1369c6fd723
msgid ""
"Design a *simple* protocol for transferring logs. The less metadata (parsed "
"in log-collecting VM) the better."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/gsoc.rst:280 ced20f5abe17432f83b27436ed8d5494
msgid ""
"Implement log collecting service. Besides logs itself, should save "
"information about logs origin (VM name) and timestamp. The service should "
"*not* trust sending VM in any of those."
msgstr ""

